
#*

  An attempt to solve newspaper style word puzzles where there is 1
  essential letter and 8 possible letters which can only be used once each. 
  Incomplete.
  
  The idea is to 'cat' a dictionary to this pep script, and determine if the
  word conforms. It is necessary to hard-code the letters into the script.
  The accumulator is used for *state*: if the essential letter is 
  found then accumulator is incremented.
  
NOTES 

  This is not the strength of the [nom] language, but I am just curious if it
  is possible.

  It is proving quite tricky to do this, especially to debug the script.
  also there is a bug in the mark/go code in the pep interpreter.
  what happens when several cells are marked with the same tag????

